%F A283971 a(2*n) = A022998(n), a(1+2*n) = 1 + 2*n.
%F A283971 a(n) = 2*a(n-4) - a(n-8).
%F A283971 From _Colin Barker_, Mar 19 2017: (Start)
%F A283971 G.f.: x*(1 + x + 3*x^2 + 4*x^3 + 3*x^4 + x^5 + x^6) / ((1 - x)^2*(1 + x)^2*(1 + x^2)^2).
%F A283971 a(n) = -((-1)^n - (-i)^n - i^n - 7)*n/8, where i = sqrt(-1).
%F A283971 (End)
%F A283971 a(n) = A060819(n) * periodic sequence of length 4: repeat [4, 1, 1, 1].
%F A283971 a(n) = a(n-4) + periodic sequence of length 4: repeat [4, 4, 2, 4].
%F A283971 From _Werner Schulte_, Jul 08 2018: (Start)
%F A283971 For n > 0, a(n) is multiplicative with a(p^e) = p^e for prime p >= 2 and e >= 0 except a(2^1) = 1.
%F A283971 Dirichlet g.f.: (1 - 1/2^s - 1/2^(2*s-1)) * zeta(s-1).
%F A283971 (End)
%F A283971 a(n) = n*(7 + cos(n*Pi/2) - cos(n*Pi) + cos(3*n*Pi/2))/8. - _Wesley Ivan Hurt_, Oct 04 2018
%F A283971 E.g.f.: (1/4)*x*(4*cosh(x) - sin(x) + 3*sinh(x)). - _Franck Maminirina Ramaharo_, Nov 13 2018
%F A283971 Sum_{k=1..n} a(k) ~ (7/16) * n^2. - _Amiram Eldar_, Nov 28 2022
